<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>Simple Form</title>
</head>
<body>

    <h2>Student Form</h2>

    <form>
        Name: <input type="text" name="name"><br><br>

        Email: <input type="email" name="email"><br><br>

        Gender:
        <input type="radio" name="gender"> Male
        <input type="radio" name="gender"> Female<br><br>

        Date of Birth:
        <input type="date" name="dob"><br><br>

        <input type="submit" value="Submit">
    </form>

</body>
</html>



Code explanation
•	<!DOCTYPE html> — tells the browser this is an HTML5 page. 
•	<html> — root element of the page. 
•	<head> — contains page information. 
•	<title> — text shown on the browser tab. 
•	<body> — visible part of the webpage. 
Form
<form>
Creates a form to take user input.
Name field
<input type="text" name="name">
Creates a normal text box for entering the name.
Email field
<input type="email" name="email">
Creates an email input box.
Gender field
<input type="radio" name="gender">
Creates radio buttons.
Both buttons have the same name, so only one option can be selected.
Date of birth
<input type="date" name="dob">
Creates a date picker.
Submit button
<input type="submit" value="Submit">
Creates a submit button.
________________________________________
Short viva explanation
If teacher says “Explain your program,” you can say:
“This program creates a simple HTML form. It takes name, email, gender, and date of birth from the user. The submit button sends the entered data.”
